Low Overhead Clustering Software
text:
Is there any low level software for 32 bit x86 that just does clustering and presents the cluster as a single virtual machine with many cores and share memory, disk.

Basically I am looking to take a bunch of x86 systems tie them together to make a unified virtual machine and then run a higher level OS on the virtual machine as if it was one computer. Local node RAM would appear as cache for the local CPU.

I am aware I can install linux on each node and make a beowulf cluster but I am wondering if there is a cleaner, lower level solution.

This is a hobbyist project at this point.
